Drum reported that while the singer was attending a jazz festival in Singapore, the scammers reportedly took advantage of her absence and asked for money from some of her contacts."When we suspected that someone had hacked into my account I asked Vodacom to block my number. But now when I came back they said they can t unblock it, she explained, although she added that it was later unblocked.Two of Winnie's close friends allegedly came forward saying that they were lured into sending money to a person they believed was the gospel star. The crooks told Winnie's friends that the money was was needed urgently to pay for a fine and directed them to a store money transfer and e-Wallet respectively.